# Protos-Web

Live: https://www.protosweb.eu · Repo: ProtosEschatos/Protos-Web · Supabase: `laqnnzavwbojntfiqmxj`

## Repo roles (mandatory)

- **This repo** = production code only. Rules **guard** the codebase; they do not replace product decisions.
- **Protos-Agent** = sessions, plans, long-term memory (`memory/projects/protos-web.md`). **Never duplicate** that content here.
- Do not bulk-edit `.cursorrules`, `AGENTS.md`, or docs unless the user asks. One feature at a time.

## Stack

Next.js 16 App Router · React 19 · TypeScript · Tailwind · next-intl · **Supabase (sole backend)** · Vercel.

**Not Convex** — ignore Convex plugin rules; this project does not use Convex.

## Before you work

1. Secrets placement: `docs/security.md` — `ADMIN_SECRET` on Vercel only, never Supabase.
2. Admin UI: `docs/admin-console.md`
3. Full memory: Protos-Agent GitHub `memory/projects/protos-web.md`
4. Architecture: `docs/architecture.md`

## Deploy

- **CI only on push:** `git push origin main` → `ci.yml` (lint + typecheck + build)
- **Vercel** — samo Next.js host; Edge email/Stripe/keep-alive su na Supabaseu (vidi `docs/security.md` → Vercel env)
- **Never** Vercel CLI
- Supabase migrations/functions: dedicated GitHub workflows (backend unchanged)

## Cursor plugins

**Disable:** Convex, Prisma, Vercel, Firebase, Pinecone, Render — ORM rules are NOT for this repo.  
**Enable:** continual-learning (memory), Supabase MCP (one). Full list: `docs/cursor-stack.md`

## ORM rules

Prisma/Convex plugin rules are marketplace defaults for other stacks. Protos-Web uses **Supabase only** — no `schema.prisma`, no `convex/`. They mislead the agent if enabled.

## Supabase clients

- Public reads: `src/lib/supabase.ts` singleton + `src/lib/supabase/env.ts`
- Admin writes: `src/lib/supabase-admin.ts` (service role)
- Do not add duplicate Supabase client wrappers

## Agent memory

- **Write** sessions/plans/learnings → **Protos-Agent** repo only
- **Read** in app: `src/lib/agent-memory.ts` → `/admin/memory`
- Never hardcode machine filesystem paths in committed code

## Env files

- Do not touch `.env*` unless the user explicitly asks
- Env vars: `.env.example` (see `docs/compatibility.md`)
- Compatibility: `docs/compatibility.md`

## Features

- **Fix, don't remove** user-facing features (3D showcase, backgrounds, nav) without explicit user approval
- Showcase `/portfolio`: no Header/Footer/SiteBackground; phases `intro` | `playing`
- Showcase must bypass site boot veil (`ShowcaseBootBypass`); use `ShowcasePrefetchLink` for entry links
- DOM = UI chrome; Canvas = 3D only (`src/components/three/**`)
- Minimize diff scope; match existing style and CSS variables
- Croatian copy for admin-facing strings

## Verify

`npm run lint && npm run type-check && npm run build` before push.
